<![CDATA[NOP();]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="53" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[This will check main read buffer for new modbus string.
First check the header, response should be at least 
8 bytes.Bytes 4 an 5 will contain additional packet length.
If all bytes of this message are received, the packet will be extracted from the Main read buffer and parsed.
Revised in Ver 2.04]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[EQU(Wrk_MSGStep,600)MOV(610,Wrk_MSGStep)GEQ(Wrk_Main_Read_Buffer.LEN,8)[COP(Wrk_Main_Read_Buffer.DATA[4],Wrk_AdditionalLen,1) SWPB(Wrk_AdditionalLen,REVERSE,Wrk_AdditionalLen1) ADD(Wrk_AdditionalLen1,6,Wrk_AdditionaLenRead) ,GEQ(Wrk_AdditionaLenRead,8) GEQ(Wrk_Main_Read_Buffer.LEN,Wrk_AdditionaLenRead) [MID(Wrk_Main_Read_Buffer,Wrk_AdditionaLenRead,1,Wrk_ModbusPacket) ,DELETE(Wrk_Main_Read_Buffer,Wrk_AdditionaLenRead,1,Wrk_Main_Read_Buffer) ,OTE(Wrk_DataReceived) ] ];]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="54" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[Check for malformed packets by checking transaction type and protocol identifier.   Clear the buffer  if found.  
This is just a safety measure in case corrupt data ever gets left in the buffer.
]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[EQU(Wrk_MSGStep,610)MOV(620,Wrk_MSGStep)XIO(Wrk_DataReceived)MOV(690,Wrk_MSGStep)[NEQ(Wrk_Main_Read_Buffer.DATA[2],0) ,NEQ(Wrk_Main_Read_Buffer.DATA[3],0) ,MOV(Wrk_Main_Read_Buffer.DATA[8],Wrk_CmdFromReadPacket) LES(Wrk_CmdFromReadPacket,1) ,GRT(Wrk_CmdFromReadPacket,6) NEQ(Wrk_CmdFromReadPacket,15) NEQ(Wrk_CmdFromReadPacket,16) ]FLL(0,Wrk_Main_Read_Buffer,1);]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="55" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[Once data is ready,  extract the Modbus_ID, Modbus_Unit, and extract the data packet from the Modbus TCP packet
Revised in V2.04]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[EQU(Wrk_MSGStep,620)MOV(625,Wrk_MSGStep)[SUB(Wrk_AdditionalLen1,1,Wrk_ModbusBytes) FLL(0,Wrk_ModbusID,1) FLL(0,Wrk_ModbusUnit,1) FLL(0,Wrk_ModbusCmdString,1) ,CLR(Wrk_CmdFromReadPacket) CLR(Wrk_ModbusTransID) ];]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="56" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[Once data is ready,  extract the Modbus_ID, Modbus_Unit, and extract the data packet from the Modbus TCP packet
revised in V2.04]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[EQU(Wrk_MSGStep,625)MOV(630,Wrk_MSGStep)EQU(Wrk_ModbusPacket.LEN,Wrk_AdditionaLenRead)[MID(Wrk_ModbusPacket,2,1,Wrk_ModbusID) MUL(Wrk_ModbusID.DATA[0],256,Wrk_ModbusTransID) OR(Wrk_ModbusID.DATA[1],Wrk_ModbusTransID,Wrk_ModbusTransID) MID(Wrk_ModbusPacket,1,7,Wrk_ModbusUnit) ,MID(Wrk_ModbusPacket,Wrk_ModbusBytes,8,Wrk_ModbusCmdString) MOV(Wrk_ModbusCmdString.DATA[0],Wrk_CmdFromReadPacket) ];]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="57" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[For these transaction types (all writes), the only thing necessary is to mark the Transaction ID as received  
AOI _CheckWriteReply will match the transaction code to the request and mark the packet as received.

]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[EQU(Wrk_MSGStep,630)MOV(640,Wrk_MSGStep)[EQU(Wrk_CmdFromReadPacket,5) ,EQU(Wrk_CmdFromReadPacket,6) ,EQU(Wrk_CmdFromReadPacket,15) ,EQU(Wrk_CmdFromReadPacket,16) ]MOV(690,Wrk_MSGStep)raC_Tec_NetModbusTCPClient_ChkWrReply(Wrk_CWR,Ref_Transactions,Wrk_ModbusTransID,Wrk_ModbusBytes,Wrk_CmdFromReadPacket,Wrk_LastTransaction);]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="58" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[Analyze incoming command for bit read commands
Trans Type 1.
Addresses 0xxxx  handling
For Transaction types of 1 and 2, call Sub_Check_Write_Reply to match Transaction code and mark received, 
then AOI _RespStrBit to parse the data and write it to the local data arrays.]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[EQU(Wrk_MSGStep,640)MOV(650,Wrk_MSGStep)EQU(Wrk_CmdFromReadPacket,1)MOV(690,Wrk_MSGStep)[MOV(Wrk_ModbusCmdString.DATA[1],Wrk_ModbusCmdLen) raC_Tec_NetModbusTCPClient_ChkWrReply(Wrk_CWR,Ref_Transactions,Wrk_ModbusTransID,Wrk_ModbusBytes,Wrk_CmdFromReadPacket,Wrk_LastTransaction) ,XIC(Wrk_CWR.TransFound) CMP(Wrk_CWR.Count<=Wrk_ModbusCmdLen*8) raC_Tec_NetModbusTCPClient_RespStrBit(Wrk_RSB,0,Wrk_CWR.Count,Wrk_CWR.LocalOffset,Ref_ModbusData,Wrk_ModbusCmdString) ];]]>
</Text>
